my meal planner is finally here!!! and she is FREE!
.
if it wasn’t already obvious from this video, i take meal planning and grocery shopping very seriously lol. the prep work before you go to the store is so worth it to make the most of the trip (the goal is to only go to the store once a week!). i’ve created a process that ensures i don’t forget any ingredients, that i don’t waste the food that i buy, that i dont spend time figuring out what I should make for dinner after work, AND that my meals are balanced and delicious. 

i’ve been testing this meal planner out for a few months now, making adjustments over time, and it has made the meal planning and grocery shopping process SO much easier. it allows you to get a holistic look at what you’ll be eating for the week, see what groceries you need and what you don’t, and i even added a little section for other weekly goals ✨ 

you can print it in color or black & white, or fill it in digitally! link in bio to download for free 🫶🏼

#mealplan #mealplanner #mealplanning #groceryshopping #fridgeorganization

more on each phase below! ✨ 
 .
i’ve spent the past few weeks learning about my cycle and how each phase effects my mind and body. ive always fought *against* my cycle, not with it, and I’ve learned so much about how that can negatively effect my body, hormones, recovery times and so much more. i’ve started syncing my cycle and workouts and its been wild to see how much better I feel throughout the month. If you want to learn more about this topic but don’t know where to start, SYNCD from @alomoves compiles virtual workouts for each phase that you can take anytime, anywhere (and they’re currently offering one month free!!). more on each phase below:
 
MENSTRATION | Day 1-5: your uterus lining is shedding, so be patient with yourself and give into slowness with gentle yoga and pilates classes. 
 
FOLLICULAR| Day 5-14: this is when your body is growing the best follicle from the ovary for that cycle. you’ll feel more uplifted, and training will feel easier on your body thanks to quicker recovery times.
 
OVULATION | Day 14-15: when the most mature egg is released from the ovary and is ready for fertilization, you’re at your peak. it’s a great time for higher intensity workouts and being extra social with friends.
 
LUTEAL | Day 15-28: if the egg isn’t fertilized, your body prepares to start the process over again and PMS symptoms can creep in. focus on low-impact workouts.
 
#cyclesyncing #alomovesparnter #hormonehealth #fitnessjourney #womenshealth #workoutroutine

southwest chickpea & chipotle ranch wrap 🙌🏼

i made this one up as i went and it turned out even better than i was thinking it would! you get lots of plant based protein thanks to the crispy barbecue chickpeas and the black beans, and the vegan chipotle ranch is literal perfection. a 10/10 lunch that takes 15 minutes (ish) to make! 
.
crispy chickpeas:
+ 1 15oz can chickpeas, drained and rinsed 
+ bake in air fryer for 10-12 mins at 400F
+ once done cooking, toss in your favorite barbecue sauce 
.
wrap ingredients:
+ burrito sized wrap 
+ romaine 
+ black beans
+ corn 
+ red onion 
+ cherry tomatoes 
+ avocado
+ cilantro (optional) 
.
vegan chipotle ranch (not giving exact measurements! measure with your heart):
+ around 1/3 cup plain vegan yogurt 
+ garlic powder, to taste
+ onion powder, to taste 
+ dried dill, to taste 
+ lil bit of lemon juice 
+ pinch of chipotle peppers in adobo for that smoky flavor 
.
how to:
roast your chickpeas and toss in your fav barbecue sauce when they’re done. while those are baking, prep your “salad” by adding the romaine, beans, veggies and homemade vegan chipotle ranch to a bowl and mixing to combine. when ready to assemble, add the salad to your tortilla, then your chickpeas, and top off with some avocado slices. wrap it up and add it to a pan over medium heat to seal and warm through. enjoy! 

#lunchideas #lunchtime #15minutemeals #easyrecipes #healthyfood

more details below ✨
.
the sunday seven is a list of tasks you can do when you want to set yourself up for a productive week ahead but you don’t know where to start. while completing all of the tasks is ideal, the seven are just guidelines and there shouldn’t be a pressure to complete them all. it is about what you CAN do, not about what you CAN’T! having this list will take the guessing game out of “what should I do with the time I have?” so that you can instead spend that time getting stuff done. the sunday seven tasks include:

1. grocery shopping - plan out your key meals and get the food you need for them.
2. food prep - wash produce and prep other key food items so that it saves you time throughout the week. this is way less time intensive than meal prep, but still has a big payoff.
3. laundry - I always do at least one load of laundry on sundays. its an easy task to complete on those days where you want to feel like you accomplished something.
4. clean your space - this doesn’t have to be a super deep clean; at the very least, get rid of clutter so that your space is usable and peaceful. clean home = clean mind.
5. exercise - go on a walk, lift some weights, do your favorite group fitness class - just move your body for the joy of it!
6. wash your sheets - the feeling of getting into a clean bed on a sunday night is truly unmatched. something about a clean bed really helps me go into the new week feeling fresh.
7. 1-3 hours (or more!) of self-care. it’s so important that we take the time to care for ourselves. grab a book, do a spa day, make your favorite meal, whatever it is, do something for YOU! 

#sundayreset #dayinthelife #dailyvlog #productivity #routine

apple, pecan & chickpea salad with a honey mustard vinaigrette 🍎 
.
every fall i see so many salads similar to this one but ive always been skeptical of the sweet and savory vibe in a salad 😬. buuuut i made this recipe up for a lunch a few weeks back and it immediately won me over!! ive been having it multiple times a week and even my boyfriend has requested it be added to our weekly meal planner! recipe below 🫶🏼

salad:
greens of choice - i like a spring mix for this salad
pecans
red onion
apple of choice 
cheese of choice - i used vegan smoked gouda
hemp seeds - optional but a great boost of added protein! 

chickpeas:
1 15oz can of chickpeas, drained and rinsed
cover in olive oil and seasonings of choice 
i used garlic powder, a steak seasoning blend, s&p
bake in air fryer for 10-15 mins at 400F 

dressing (you might need to double this based on how big your salad is!)
1/2 tbsp olive oil 
1/2 tbsp lemon juice
1/2 tsp dijon mustard 
1/2 tsp honey 
pinch of garlic powder
s&p to taste

you don’t have to be great to start, but you do have to start to be great 🤍 

as a type-a perfectionist, it’s hard for me to do things im not good at. 

i don’t like failing and i struggle to push myself out of my comfort zone at times. but, starting my health and wellness journey 10 years ago while having zero idea what i was doing will forever be one of the best things ive ever done for myself. i knew essentially nothing about cooking, nutrition and fitness…but i knew i just needed to start somewhere. start with one recipe, or one workout, and before you know it, you’ll find yourself at the place you always wanted to be ✨

overnight oats with ~30g of protein and they taste like dessert 🙌🏼
 
the holidays typically mean a lot of travel, a lot of social gatherings, and lots of good food. i eat alllll the good food during the holidays while also making an effort to still hit my protein goals. the @truvani protein powders are a staple in my kitchen and make it so easy to get in a high protein, on-the-go breakfast. in 15 minutes i can prep 5 days worth of high protein breakfasts that help to support my blood sugar balance, give me the energy i need to start the day, and help me focus better while i work. the minimal ingredients in the powders and the variety of flavors are amazing, too! use code AVERY for 20% off 🫶🏼 #truvani #truvanipartner

base:
1/2 cup oats 
1 tbsp chia seeds 
3/4 to 1 cup soy milk of choice 
1/4 tsp vanilla extract 
pinch of salt 

vanilla chai:
1 serving Truvani vanilla chai protein 
cinnamon to taste 

lemon blueberry:
1 serving Truvani vanilla protein 
1/4 tsp lemon extract
blueberries 
lemon zest for topping 

chocolate orange: 
1 serving Truvani chocolate protein 
1/2 tbsp cacao powder 
1 tsp orange zest
2 tsp orange juice 
1/2 tbsp almond butter

chocolate peanut butter:
1 serving Truvani chocolate peanut butter protein
1/2 tbsp cacao powder 
1/2 tbsp peanut butter 
optional: chocolate chips for topping 

chocolate coconut:
1 serving Truvani chocolate protein
1/2 tbsp cacao powder 
1 tbsp shredded coconut 
1/2 tbsp almond butter 
1/8 tsp almond extract

never leaving my apartment ever again 🎄🍪 ‘tis the season of cozy nights in and i couldn’t be happier about it! give me alllll the holiday movies and cookies, like my almond flour cookie recipe using with the iconic chocolate chips by @hukitchen. made with four simple ingredients and containing no added sugar, they are a must have in my pantry! they’re the perfect addition to these crispy on the outside, doughy on the inside cooked. recipe below and use code AVERY for 20% off 🫶🏼 #hupartner #hukitchen #getbacktohuman 

- 1 3/4 cup almond flour 
- 1/2 tsp baking powder 
- pinch of salt 
- 1/2 cup maple syrup 
- 2 tbsp creamy peanut butter or almond butter 
- 1 1/2 tsp vanilla extract 
- 1/2 cup @hukitchen chocolate chips

preheat your oven to 350F. to a large bowl, add the almond flour, baking powder and salt and mix to combine. then add in the maple, almond butter or peanut butter, vanilla and mix again. then fold in the chocolate chips. form into patties and add them to a parchment lined baking sheet. bake for 15 - 20 mins, until slightly golden on the bottom. remove from oven and let them cool completely before touching.
